cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.NE 

This paper deals with optimization of strategies in games, which is a topic that falls under game theory (cs.GT). The use of evolutionary algorithms and coevolution also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The study of partially observable games involves the use of probabilistic models and decision-making under uncertainty, which is relevant to systems and control theory (cs.SY). Finally, the use of stochastic optimization methods falls under the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
